text: Luneluah Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. It is a tributary to Beasha Creek. Luneluah Creek is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean "burnt frog". A variant name is "Suneluah Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Neshoba County, Mississippi
title: Luneluah Creek
